message_1:
A medical study wants to test whether a certain medication increases the average survival time of patients with a specific disease. The researchers do not know the distribution of survival times in the population, so they decide to use a non-parametric test. 

The survival times (in months) of a random sample of 12 patients who receive the medication are:

{5, 7, 9, 11, 12, 12, 13, 16, 21, 23, 25, 30}

The survival times (in months) of a random sample of 10 patients who do not receive the medication are:

{4, 6, 8, 9, 11, 15, 18, 20, 22, 25}

Can you conduct a two-sample non-parametric test to determine whether the medication increases the average survival time of patients (at 5% significance level)?
